    "summary": "After his study at the Netherlands Institute for Tourism  Breda and Columbia College , Missouri , \nHans van Driem started his career in 1970 as Tour Director Europe for USA operators.In 1974 he was sales manger USA for NBBS College Study Tours to Europe.\nIn 1975 he was assistant sales & marketing manager The Hague Marketing for the renovated beach resort Scheveningen. \nIn 1979 he joined Crest Hotels as sales & marketing manager Benelux. After various take-overs by Bass Plc he became vice-president sales & marketing Europe ( IHG ) \n\nIn 1988 he was appointed as director commercial affairs & operations of the World Horticulture Exhibition Floriade 1992. After closing the successful exhibition with 3,3 million visits, he was appointed managing director of Walibi Flevo. \nHe was responsible for the construction and operation of the new theme park and adjacent festival park with  the \u2018World Jamboree\u2019 , \u2018Lowlands Paradise\u2019. From1997 he was responsible  for the development & construction of Six Flags Holland.\nIn september 2000 he was appointed as managing director  Netherlands Board of Tourism and Conventions NBTC. Various mergers and reorganisations were executed  to develop  NBTC in a commercial & professional International DMO. A redesigned Holland.com and successful event Rembrandt 400, resulted in a record of 10 million tourists to Holland 2006.\nFrom March 2007 he was managing director of  Holland Business Promotion Office .HBPO was to coordinate the international  promotion of economic sectors of Holland at OS 2008 and World Expo 2010.\n\nIn 2011 he started International Destination Strategies. IDS is specialized in the design briefing of the creative concept & brand strategy, with regards to the project development of public private , \nmulti brand leisure destinations, with retail, food & beverage, hospitality and location-based entertainment experiences.\n\n IDS has been involved in the development of projects in China, France, Holland, India, Poland ,Thailand & UAE.\n\nSpecialties: Development, design, construction , operations , sales & marketing of large hospitality, leisure & entertaiment facilities",
